<h2 id="instructions">Instructions</h2>

<p>Write a program that accepts the lengths of three sides of a triangle as inputs. The program output should indicate whether or not the triangle is a right triangle.</p>

<p>Recall from the Pythagorean theorem that in a right triangle, the square of one side equals the sum of the squares of the other two sides.</p>

<p>Use The triangle is a right triangle. and The triangle is not a right triangle. as your final outputs.
An example of the program input and proper output format is shown below:</p>

<div class="language-text highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Enter the first side : 3
Enter the second side: 4
Enter the third side : 5

The triangle is a right triangle.
</code></pre></div></div>

<blockquote>
  <p>Any of the three sides of the triangle could be the hypotenuse. The program should handle this appropriately.</p>
</blockquote>

